<p>President Trump has had the White House East Wing razed to make way for a new ballroom, with satellite imagery confirming the demolition this week and the administration saying the space will be rebuilt for large events . The president has said the roughly $300 million project will be paid for by him “and some friends of mine,” and aides have solicited private donors to help fund the work . The move has drawn complaints from preservationists and historians who say the East Wing includes historically significant first ladies’ offices, while White House aides and some supporters defend the plan as an expansion for official entertaining and fundraising activity .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/t1oka1E7GzrnnVVUhc5g9-2tQVkrBYhounwh5xr5dMFwzRiENAGSk6T2flm9zjlhHwAM_h7oW5zCkmHFfYp6U4mh-5VmwKJfznuq33wfwbenSIFzGcxsY18W9d1y4R5Llyx7Mq6OjUhi3SEg78z0DsXwgjSPWJCcQM0' alt='Coverage image linked to reports that President Trump is considering naming the new White House ballroom after himself' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Who’s paying: Reporting identifies prospective private backers including tech giants, crypto industry figures and tobacco groups who have been approached to bankroll parts of the project .</li><li>Possible naming: Officials and reports say President Trump is considering naming the new space after himself, though he declined to discuss that possibility when asked .</li><li>Public reaction: Images of the demolition have prompted sharp public commentary and satirical cartoons across outlets, reflecting a strong visual reaction to the change at the presidential residence .</li><li>Donor gatherings: Reporters say Mr Trump recently told donors a real-estate style story about the project during a meeting earlier this month, illustrating active private fundraising efforts tied to the plan .</li></ul><blockquote>I won’t get into that now. - President Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>The president and White House aides: The administration says the new ballroom will be rebuilt for official entertaining and that private contributions and the president&#x27;s own funds will cover costs. (<a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/white-house-east-wing-razed-to-make-way-for-trumps-300-million-ballroom/'>Times of Israel</a>)</li><li>Stephen Miller (advisor): Stephen Miller insisted the East Wing &#x27;is not part of the White House&#x27; while defending changes to the building footprint. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2025/oct/24/donald-trump-trade-negotiations-canada-mark-carney-terminated-tariff-letitia-james-new-york-us-politics-live-news'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Preservationists and historians: Historic preservation groups and historians have expressed dismay at the demolition, saying the East Wing contains historically significant first ladies&#x27; offices. (<a href='https://www.allsides.com/news/2025-10-24-0700/donald-trump-white-house-sideswiped-ballroom-demolition-controversy'>AllSides</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/1f737c7c-74ee-4b8f-b601-ad83dae6d801'>Trump flattens East Wing as donors bankroll gilded White House project</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.allsides.com/news/2025-10-24-0700/donald-trump-white-house-sideswiped-ballroom-demolition-controversy'>White House sideswiped by ballroom demolition controversy</a> - allsides.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/videos/c4gkrnn4892o'>Satellite images show extent of demolition at the White House</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/white-house-east-wing-razed-to-make-way-for-trumps-300-million-ballroom/'>White House East Wing razed to make way for Trump’s $300-million ballroom</a> - timesofisrael.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2025/oct/24/donald-trump-trade-negotiations-canada-mark-carney-terminated-tariff-letitia-james-new-york-us-politics-live-news'>Trump adviser Stephen Miller insists East Wing of White House ‘is no